_meanings:
{@--1@} To curse, execrate; {#aSapadBava#} 
{#mAnuzIti tAM#} <ls>R. 8. 80</ls>; {#so'BUtparAsuraTa#} 
{#BUmipatiM SaSApa (vfdDaH)#} <ls n="R.">9. 78</ls>, <ls n="R.">1. 77.</ls>

{@--2@} To
swear, take an oath, promise by
oath, say on oath, (usually with
<ab>dat.</ab> of the person to whom a 
promise &c. is made and <ab>instr.</ab> of the
object by which it is made);  
{#BaratenAtpanA cAhaM Sape te manujADipa . yaTA#} 
{#nAnyena tuzyeyamfte rAmavivAsanAt#} Rām;
when used without an object it
generally governs the <ab>instr.</ab> of the
thing and <ab>dat.</ab> of the person by
which or whom the oath is taken;
{#satyaM SapAmi ne pAdapaMkajasparSena#} <ls>K.</ls>;
<ls>Ghaṭ. 22</ls>; {#aSapta nihnuvAnA'sO sItAyE#}
{#smaramohitaH#} <ls>Bk. 8. 74</ls>; {#prema#} 
{#jijYAsamAnAbyastAbyo'Sapsata kAminaH#} <ls n="Bk.">8. 33</ls>; 
sometimes {#Sap#} governs a cognate 
accusative {#sahatraSo'sO SapaTAnaSapyat#}  
<ls>Bk. 3. 32.</ls>

{@--3@} To blame, scold, revile, abuse
(with dat or by itself);  
{#dvizadByaScASapastayA#} <ls>Bk. 17. 4.</ls> {#prativAcamadatta#} 
{#keSavaH SapamAnAya na cediBUBuje#}  
<ls>Śi. 16 25.</ls>

To bind by
an oath, conjure; {#SApito'si#} 
{#gobrAhmaRakAmyayA#} <ls>Mk. 3</ls>; {#SApitAsi mama#} 
{#lavaMgikAvalokitayoSva jIvitena yadi vAcA na#}
{#kaTayasi#} <ls>Māl. 8.</ls>
